---
description: DIMO integration rules
globs:
  - "**/*dimo*"
  - "**/*telemetry*"
  - "**/*segments*"
  - "**/*webhook*"
  - "**/*trigger*"
  - "**/*agent*"
---

When working on DIMO-related code:

- Use the DIMO MCP server for guidance and verification.
- Inspect existing DIMO auth, telemetry, segments, event, DTC, worker, and webhook logic before changing anything.
- DIMO Segments are the source of truth for trip boundaries where that architecture applies.
- Historical signals may reconstruct route geometry inside segment time windows, not redefine canonical trip boundaries.
- Do not invent local fallback logic when the intended DIMO integration path exists.
- Verify request/response shape, auth, vehicle access, and trigger registration before implementing changes.
- Preserve shared DIMO service/client architecture.
